posts.name: Thad House
posts.cooked:
Do you only get that message once at the beginning of running code? If so, because of how the CAN setup is implemented that is not super surprising of an error.

If that is the case, are you sure the solenoid is not activating? Do you have your code somewhere to review?

posts.name: NewtonCrosby
posts.cooked: Can you put your code on Github so we can see it easily?

posts.name: Debbie Bernier
posts.cooked:
The code is in a zip file attached to the original post.  Are you able to download it? I zipped up the src folder (and everything beneath it).  If the zip attachment doesn’t work, let me know and I’ll see if I can find another place to put it.

And I’m sure the solenoid isn’t activating. And the compressor doesn’t turn on either (which it’s supposed to do when you create a solenoid object)

posts.name: Fletch
posts.cooked:
If you’re sharing a zip because you’re not using source control (i.e. git/github), then you should absolutely look into it.

If you’re doing so out of concern for secrecy or something like that, well, I don’t quite understand the concern, but fair enough.

posts.name: Brian Gaffey
posts.cooked: Is your PCM running the latest firmware version and is it still on the default CAN device id of 0?

posts.name: Debbie Bernier
posts.cooked: The firmware has been updated in the PCM (we’re using the new Rev module which was in the KoP). We also have the new Power Distribution hub which we also updated the firmware on. The PCM and PDH have CAN IDs 1 which I assumed was ok since they are different device types. We also have a Spark Max on that same board which also has a CAN id of 1.

posts.name: Debbie Bernier
posts.cooked: Actually we do use Git and Github but our repo is private (team lead decision…I don’t have the power to change that) so I’d have to move the code to another repo to share it.

posts.name: Debbie Bernier
posts.cooked: Found it! My mistake was not updating the code to reflect that we changed the PCM from CTRE to Rev.

posts.name: Erdinç
posts.cooked: I found the problem, port should be given at 0 Can connection in PCM
